**Example Improvement:**

```java
public class SecurityProxy<T> implements T {
    private final T target;
    private final AuthenticationService authService;

    public SecurityProxy(T target, AuthenticationService authService) {
        this.target = target;
        this.authService = authService;
    }

    @Override
    public void someMethod() {
        // Check if user is authenticated
        if (!authService.isAuthenticated()) {
            throw new UnauthorizedAccessException("User not authenticated");
        }
        // Perform authorization check
        if (!authService.isAuthorizedFor(target)) {
            throw new AuthorizationDeniedException("User does not have permission");
        }
        // Delegate to the original object
        target.someMethod();
    }
}
```

This example shows how the proxy can be initialized with the original object and an authentication service, and how it enforces security checks before delegating methods to the original object.

